abstract: CANTON, Ohio, Sept. 29 -- John W. Foster, ex-Secretary of State, slipped quietly into Canton this morning, and had an hour's talk with Major McKinley. He said, before leaving, that Indiana would give a very substantial plurality for McKinley, and that he would get the votes of most of the gold Democrats.
